Float.Description: Maximum number of frames that can be transferred per second with current camera settings. This value indicates the peak frame rate to be expected at the camera's output. In High Speed burst mode, this value is usually lower than the Resulting Acquisition Frame Rate parameter value.

Enumeration.Name: ExposureAuto
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the operation mode of the Exposure Auto auto function.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the operation mode of the Exposure Auto auto function. The Exposure Auto auto function automatically adjusts the exposure time within set limits until a target brightness value has been reached.

EnumEntry.Name: Off
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Automatic exposure time adjustment is disabled.
EnumEntry.Description: Automatic exposure time adjustment is disabled.

EnumEntry.Name: Once
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The exposure time is adjusted automatically to reach the specified target value.
EnumEntry.Description: The exposure time is adjusted automatically to reach the specified target value. When the target value has been reached, the auto function will automatically be set to Off and the new parameter value will be applied to the following images.

EnumEntry.Name: Continuous
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The exposure time is adjusted continuously while images are being acquired.
EnumEntry.Description: The exposure time is adjusted continuously while images are being acquired. The adjustment process will continue until the parameter is set to Once or Off.

Integer.Name: SensorWidth
Integer.ToolTip: Width of the camera's sensor in pixels.
Integer.Description: Width of the camera's sensor in pixels.

Integer.Name: SensorHeight
Integer.ToolTip: Height of the camera's sensor in pixels.
Integer.Description: Height of the camera's sensor in pixels.

Boolean.Name: ReverseX
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables horizontal mirroring of the image.
Boolean.Description: Enables horizontal mirroring of the image. The pixel values of every line in a captured image will be swapped along the line's center. You can use the ROI feature when using the Reverse X feature. The position of the ROI relative to the sensor remains the same.

Boolean.Name: ReverseY
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables vertical mirroring of the image.
Boolean.Description: Enables vertical mirroring of the image. The pixel values of every column in a captured image will be swapped along the column's center. You can use the ROI feature when using the Reverse Y feature. The position of the ROI relative to the sensor remains the same.

Enumeration.Name: BslAcquisitionBurstMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the burst mode.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the burst mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Standard
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The Standard burst mode is enabled.
EnumEntry.Description: The Standard burst mode is enabled. This mode allows you to execute bursts in quick succession, but offers lower frame rates compared to High Speed burst mode.

EnumEntry.Name: HighSpeed
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The High Speed burst mode is enabled.
EnumEntry.Description: The High Speed burst mode is enabled. This mode offers high frame rates within a burst, but introduces a delay after each burst. Within a burst, the frame rate is only limited by the bandwidth of the streaming buffer and the sensor.

Integer.Name: ActionDeviceKey
Integer.ToolTip: Device key used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Device key used to authorize the execution of an action command. If the action device key in the camera and the action device key in the protocol message are identical, the camera will execute the corresponding action.

Integer.Name: ActionQueueSize
Integer.ToolTip: Number of action commands that can be queued by the camera.
Integer.Description: Number of action commands that can be queued by the camera. The camera will execute them in ascending order of action time. If the queue is full, additional commands will be ignored.

Integer.Name: ActionSelector
Integer.ToolTip: Action command to be configured.
Integer.Description: Action command to be configured.

Integer.Name: ActionGroupKey
Integer.ToolTip: Group key used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Group key used to define a group of cameras on which action commands can be executed.

Integer.Name: ActionGroupMask
Integer.ToolTip: Group mask used for action commands.
Integer.Description: Group mask used to filter out a sub-group of cameras belonging to a group of cameras. The cameras belonging to a sub-group execute an action at the same time. The filtering is done using a logical bitwise AND operation on the group mask number of the action command and the group mask number of a camera. If both binary numbers have at least one common bit set to 1 (i.e., the result of the AND operation is non-zero), the corresponding camera belongs to the sub-group.

Integer.Name: DigitalShift
Integer.ToolTip: Digital shift to be applied.
Integer.Description: Digital shift allows you to multiply the pixel values in an image. This increases the brightness of the image. If the parameter is set to zero, digital shift is disabled.

Integer.Name: LineStatusAll
Integer.ToolTip: Single bit field indicating the current logical state of all available line signals at time of polling.
Integer.Description: Single bit field indicating the current logical state of all available line signals at time of polling.

Integer.Name: UserOutputValueAll
Integer.ToolTip: Single bit field that sets the state of all user-settable output signals in one access.
Integer.Description: Single bit field that sets the state of all user-settable output signals in one access.

Integer.Name: BslLineOverloadStatusAll
Integer.ToolTip: Single bit field indicating which GPIO lines are overloaded, i.e., not powered correctly, at time of polling.
Integer.Description: Single bit field indicating which GPIO lines are overloaded, i.e., not powered correctly, at time of polling.

Float.Name: AutoTargetBrightness
Float.ToolTip: Target brightness for the Gain Auto and the Exposure Auto auto functions.
Float.Description: Target brightness for the Gain Auto and the Exposure Auto auto functions.

Enumeration.Name: AutoFunctionProfile
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets how gain and exposure time will be balanced when the camera is making automatic adjustments.
Enumeration.Description: Sets how gain and exposure time will be balanced when the camera is making automatic adjustments.

EnumEntry.Name: MinimizeGain
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Gain is kept as low as possible.
EnumEntry.Description: Gain is kept as low as possible during automatic adjustments.

EnumEntry.Name: MinimizeExposureTime
EnumEntry.ToolTip: Exposure time is kept as low as possible.
EnumEntry.Description: Exposure time is kept as low as possible during automatic adjustments.

Float.Name: AutoGainLowerLimit
Float.ToolTip: Lower limit of the Gain parameter when the Gain Auto auto function is active.
Float.Description: Lower limit of the Gain parameter when the Gain Auto auto function is active.

Float.Name: AutoGainUpperLimit
Float.ToolTip: Upper limit of the Gain parameter when the Gain Auto auto function is active.
Float.Description: Upper limit of the Gain parameter when the Gain Auto auto function is active.

Float.Name: AutoExposureTimeLowerLimit
Float.ToolTip: Lower limit of the Exposure Time parameter when the Exposure Auto auto function is active.
Float.Description: Lower limit of the Exposure Time parameter when the Exposure Auto auto function is active.

Float.Name: AutoExposureTimeUpperLimit
Float.ToolTip: Upper limit of the Exposure Time parameter when the Exposure Auto auto function is active.
Float.Description: Upper limit of the Exposure Time parameter when the Exposure Auto auto function is active.

Integer.Name: Width
Integer.ToolTip: Width of the camera's region of interest (area of interest) in pixels.
Integer.Description: Width of the camera's region of interest (area of interest) in pixels. Depending on the camera model, the parameter can be set in different increments.

Integer.Name: Height
Integer.ToolTip: Height of the camera's region of interest (area of interest) in pixels.
Integer.Description: Height of the camera's region of interest (area of interest) in pixels. Depending on the camera model, the parameter can be set in different increments.

Integer.Name: OffsetX
Integer.ToolTip: Horizontal offset of the region of interest (area of interest) from the left side of the sensor (in pixels).
Integer.Description: Horizontal offset from the left side of the sensor to the region of interest (area of interest) (in pixels).

Integer.Name: OffsetY
Integer.ToolTip: Vertical offset of the region of interest (area of interest) from the top of the sensor (in pixels).
Integer.Description: Vertical offset from the top of the sensor to the region of interest (area of interest) (in pixels).

Integer.Name: WidthMax
Integer.ToolTip: Maximum width of the region of interest (area of interest) in pixels.
Integer.Description: Maximum width of the region of interest (area of interest) in pixels. The value takes into account any function that may limit the maximum width.

Integer.Name: HeightMax
Integer.ToolTip: Maximum height of the region of interest (area of interest) in pixels.
Integer.Description: Maximum height of the region of interest (area of interest) in pixels. The value takes into account any features that may limit the maximum height, e.g., binning.

Command.Description: Centers the image horizontally.

Command.Name: BslCenterY
Command.ToolTip: Centers the image vertically.
Command.Description: Centers the image vertically.

Boolean.Name: BslMultipleROIColumnsEnable
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables or disables the ability to define multiple regions in horizontal direction.
Boolean.Description: Enables or disables the ability to define multiple regions in horizontal direction. When disabled, the width and horizontal offset of all regions is defined by the Width and Offset X parameters, and the Multiple ROI Column Offset and Multiple ROI Column Size parameter values are ignored.

Boolean.Name: BslMultipleROIRowsEnable
Boolean.ToolTip: Enables or disables the ability to define multiple regions in vertical direction.
Boolean.Description: Enables or disables the ability to define multiple regions in vertical direction. When disabled, the height and vertical offset of all regions is defined by the Height and Offset Y parameters, and the Multiple ROI Row Offset and Multiple ROI Row Size parameter values are ignored.

Float.Description: Gamma correction to be applied. Gamma correction allows you to optimize the brightness of acquired images for display on a monitor.

Float.Name: BslContrast
Float.ToolTip: Contrast value to be applied.
Float.Description: Adjusting the contrast increases the difference between light and dark areas in the image.

Enumeration.Name: BslContrastMode
Enumeration.ToolTip: Sets the contrast mode.
Enumeration.Description: Sets the contrast mode.

EnumEntry.Name: Linear
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The camera uses a linear function to adjust the contrast.
EnumEntry.Description: The camera uses a linear function to adjust the contrast. Increasing or decreasing the contrast, increases or decreases the gradient of the linear function.

EnumEntry.Name: SCurve
EnumEntry.ToolTip: The camera uses an S-curve function to adjust the contrast.
EnumEntry.Description: The camera uses an S-curve function to adjust the contrast. This allows you to improve the perceived contrast while preserving the dynamic range of the image.

Float.Name: BslBrightness
Float.ToolTip: Brightness value to be applied.
Float.Description: Adjusting the brightness lightens or darkens the entire image.
